rts/docs/Macmini_PER_oct2014.pdf |archivedate=October 16, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n!Mode !!100&nbsp;V !!115&nbsp;V !!230&nbsp;V\n|-\n|Off ||0.29&nbsp;W ||0.29&nbsp;W ||0.31&nbsp;W\n|-\n|Sleep ||0.75&nbsp;W ||0.71&nbsp;W ||0.73&nbsp;W\n|-\n|Idle ||5.9&nbsp;W ||5.8&nbsp;W ||5.5&nbsp;W\n|}\n|-\n|'''Greenhouse gas emissions'''\n|| {{convert|270|kg|lb|abbr=on}} CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\"mid2010environreport\"/>\n|| {{convert|710|kg|lb|abbr=on}} CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\"mid2010serverenvironreport\"/>\n|colspan=2| {{convert|280|kg|lb|abbr=on}} CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\"mid2011environreport\"/>\n|| {{convert|1130|kg|lb|abbr=on}} CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\"mid2011serverenvironreport\"/>\n|colspan=2| {{convert|290|kg|lb|abbr=on}} CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\"late2012environreport\"/>\n|| {{convert|1020|kg|lb|abbr=on}} CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\"late2012serverenvironreport\"/>\n|colspan=3| {{convert|530|kg|lb|abbr=on}} CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\"late2014environreport\"/>\n|-\n|'''Weight'''\n|| {{convert|3.0|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|| {{convert|2.8|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|colspan=2| {{convert|2.7|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|| {{convert|3.0|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|colspan=2| {{convert|2.7|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|| {{convert|2.9|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|colspan=2| {{convert|2.6|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n| {{convert|2.7|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|'''Dimensions'''\n|colspan=11|{{convert|1.4|in|mm|0}} H \u00d7 {{convert|7.7|in|mm|0}} W \u00d7 {{convert|7.7|in|mm|0}} D\n|-\n|}\n\n==4th generation (USB-C)==\n[[File:Mac mini (2018) ports.jpg|thumb|350px|Back panel of a 2018 Mac mini. From left to right, first row: power button, AC power supply plug, Gigabit Ethernet, 4 Thunderbolt 3 (USB-C 3.1 Gen 2), HDMI 2.0, 2 USB 3.0 Type-A. Second row: ventilation holes, audio out]]\nOn October 30, 2018, Apple announced a fourth generation Mac mini with Intel [[Coffee Lake]] processors, the [[Apple T series|T2]] series chip used to manage the security of the device, [[Bluetooth 5]], four [[USB-C|USB-C 3.1 gen 2]] ports that support [[Thunderbolt (interface)|Thunderbolt 3]], two USB 3.0 Type-A ports, and HDMI 2.0. PCIe-based flash storage is standard with no option of a [[hard disk drive]]. The storage was changed to a baseline 128 GB, with a maximum of 2 TB. The [[RAM]] was increased to a baseline of 8 GB, and a maximum of 64 GB of [[DDR4|SO-DIMM DDR4]]. The chassis is mostly a carryover from the previous generation, measuring the same dimensions, though is only available in a darker \"space gray\" finish.<ref>[https://www.pcmag.com/news/364698/apples-new-mac-mini-kills-the-entry-level-mac Apple's New Mac mini Kills the Entry-Level Mac]. [[PC Magazine|PC Mag]]. October 30, 2018.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/mac-mini/}}</ref> This generation removes the SD card reader, SATA drive bay, IR receiver, optical S/PDIF (TOSLINK) audio out, and audio in. [[macOS Catalina]] added support for [[Dolby Atmos]], [[Dolby Vision]], and [[HDR10]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/3/18650205/apple-macos-catalina-10-15-update-announced-features-wwdc-2019|title=Apple unveils new macOS update with iPad apps|last=Warren|first=Tom|date=June 3, 2019|website=The Verge|access-date=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020 Apple doubled the default storage in both base models.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/apples-modest-mac-mini-update-twice-the-storage-for-the-same-price/|title=Apple's modest Mac Mini update: Twice the storage for the same price|last=Jaffe|first=Justin|website=CNET|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n=== Hardware replaceability ===\nMemory can again be replaced, unlike the 2014 models which had it soldered directly to the logic board.<ref>[https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/Mac+mini+Late+2018+Memory+Replacement/115309 Mac mini Late 2018 Memory Replacement].[[iFixit]].</ref> The processor and flash storage are soldered to the logic board and cannot be replaced.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ifixit.com/Teardown/Mac+mini+Late+2018+Teardown/115210|title=Mac mini Late 2018 Teardown|date=2018-11-09|website=iFixit|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref>\n\n===Specifications===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#3d4;\"|\n| Current\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n<!-- 2 or 3 columns per release -->\n|-\n!style=\"width:5%\"| Component\n!colspan=2| Intel [[Core i7#Core i5 2|Core i3]], [[Core i7#Core i5 2|i5]], [[Core i7#Core i7 2|i7]]\n|-\n!style=width:8%\"|Model\n!colspan=2 style=\"background:#3d4;;width:20%\"|2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://support.apple.com/kb/SP782|title=Mac mini (2018) - Technical Specifications|website=support.apple.com|language=en|access-date=2018-11-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Release Date'''\n| colspan=\"2\" |November 7, 2018\n|-\n|'''Order Number'''\n|MRTR2*/A\n|MRTT2*/A\n|-\n|'''Machine Model'''\n|colspan=2|Macmini8,1\n|-\n|'''Base Price At Launch'''\n|$799\n|$1099\n|-\n|'''Model Number'''\n|colspan=2|A1993\n|-\n|'''Processor'''\n|Intel Core i3-8100B quad-core CPU <br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional Intel Core i7-8700B six-core CPU at time of purchase only''</span>\n|Intel Core i5-8500B six-core CPU <br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional Intel Core i7-8700B six-core CPU at time of purchase only''</span> \n|-\n|'''Frequency (Boost)'''\n|3.6 GHz (Core i3) or 3.2 GHz (Core i7, boost to 4.6 GHz)\n|3.0 GHz (Core i5, boost to 4.1 GHz) or 3.2 GHz (Core i7, boost to 4.6 GHz)\n|-\n|'''Cores/Threads'''\n|4/4 (Core i3), 6/12 (Core i7)\n|6/6 (Core i5), 6/12 (Core i7)\n|-\n|'''Cache'''\n|6 MB (Core i3), 12 MB (Core i7)\n|9 MB (Core i5), 12 MB (Core i7)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | '''Memory'''\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |8 GB <span style=\"color:#969696\">''(Optional upgrade at time of purchase: 16 GB/32 GB/64 GB)''</span>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |DDR4 SO-DIMM 2666 MHz\n|-\n|'''Graphics'''\n| colspan=\"2\" |[[Intel Graphics Technology#Kaby Lake Refresh / Amber Lake / Coffee Lake / Whiskey Lake / Comet Lake|Intel UHD Graphics 630]]\n|-\n|'''Video Support'''\n| colspan=\"2\" |''Support for the following combination of maximum concurrent display setups:''\n* Up to 3 displays:<br/>\n2 displays with [[4K resolution#Other 4K resolutions|4096x2304]] resolution at 60 Hz via [[Thunderbolt (interface)#Thunderbolt 3|Thunderbolt 3]], plus 1 display with [[4K resolution#4096 \u00d7 2160|4096x2160]] resolution at 60 Hz via [[HDMI#Version 2.0|HDMI 2.0]]\n\n''or''<br/>\n* Up to 2 displays:<br/>\n1 display with [[5K resolution|5120x2880]] resolution at 60 Hz via Thunderbolt 3, plus 1 display with 4096x2160 resolution at 60 Hz via HDMI 2.0<br/><br/>\n\n''Thunderbolt 3 digital video output supports''<br/>\n*Native [[DisplayPort#USB-C|DisplayPort]] 1.2 (up to 4k)<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikichip.org/wiki/intel/uhd_graphics/630#Features|title=UHD Graphics 630 - Intel Features|date=July 13, 2018|website=wikichip.org|access-date=November 28, 2018}}</ref> output over [[USB-C]]<br/>\n*Thunderbolt 2, [[Digital Visual Interface|DVI]], and [[Video Graphics Array|VGA]] output supported using adapters (sold separately)<br/>\n\n''HDMI 2.0 display video output''<br/>\n*Support for up to 1 display with 4096x2160 resolution at 60 Hz<br/>\n*DVI output using HDMI to DVI adapter (sold separately)\n|-\n| rowspan=3|'''[[Solid-state drive]]'''\n|-\n|128 GB ''(before March 2020)''<br>256 GB\n<span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional 512 GB, 1 TB, or 2 TB available at time of purchase only''</span>\n|256 GB ''(before March 2020)''<br>512 GB\n<span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional 1 TB or 2 TB available at time of purchase only''</span>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[NVM Express|NVMe]]/PCIe 3.0 \u00d74 8.0 GT/s (31.5 Gbit/s)\n|-\n|'''[[Apple-designed processors#T series|Security Chip]]'''\n|colspan=\"2\"| [[Apple-designed processors#Apple T2|Apple T2]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | '''Connectivity'''\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |Built-in [[IEEE 802.11ac|Wi-Fi 5]] (802.11a/b/g/n/ac) 3\u00d73 chipset, up to 1.3 Gbit/s\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |Bluetooth 5.0\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | Gigabit Ethernet (upgradeable to [[10 Gigabit Ethernet]] at time of purchase)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |'''Peripheral Connections'''\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | 4\u00d7 [[Thunderbolt (interface)|Thunderbolt 3]] ([[USB-C]] 3.1 Gen 2)\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | 2\u00d7 USB 3.0 Type-A\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | HDMI 2.0\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | 3.5 mm headphone jack\n|-\n|'''Noise (at idle)'''\n| colspan=\"2\" |4 dBA\n|-\n|'''Power'''\n| colspan=\"2\" |150 W (max continuous) <ref>{{cite web |title=Mac mini - Technical Specifications |url=https://www.apple.com/mac-mini/specs/ |website=Apple |publisher=Apple |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"font-size:88%\"\n! colspan=4 style=\"background:inherit;\"| {{color|#969696|''(All Models)''}}<ref name=\"2018environreport\">{{Citation |title=Product Environmental Report Mac mini |year=2018 |publisher=Apple Inc. |url=https://www.apple.com/environment/pdf/products/desktops/Macmini_PER_oct2018.pdf\n|date=October 30, 2018|accessdate=February 21, 2020 |url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n!Mode !!100&nbsp;V !!115&nbsp;V !!230&nbsp;V\n|-\n|Off ||0.34&nbsp;W ||0.31&nbsp;W ||0.34&nbsp;W\n|-\n|Sleep ||1.01&nbsp;W ||1.19&nbsp;W ||1.16&nbsp;W\n|-\n|Idle ||10.6&nbsp;W ||10.6&nbsp;W ||11.5&nbsp;W\n|}\n|-\n|'''Greenhouse Gas Emissions'''\n|226 kg CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/environment/pdf/products/desktops/Macmini_PER_oct2018.pdf|title=Product Environmental Report Mac Mini|date=October 30, 2018|website=Apple|access-date=November 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|255 kg CO<sub>2</sub>e<ref name=\":0\" />\n|-\n|'''Weight'''\n| colspan=\"2\" |1.3 kg (2.9 pounds)\n|-\n|'''Dimensions'''\n| colspan=\"2\" |3.6 cm (H) \u00d7 19.7 cm (W) \u00d7 19.7 cm (D)\n|}\n\n== Supported macOS releases ==\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible style=\"width: 100%;\" style=\"font-size: 90%;\n|-\n! colspan=\"14\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | Supported macOS releases\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:12em;\" |OS release\n! 