&nbsp;GB (2 \u00d7 2&nbsp;GB)<br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Expandable to 8&nbsp;GB (2 \u00d7 4&nbsp;GB)''</span>\n|2&nbsp;GB (2 \u00d7 1&nbsp;GB)<br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional 4 (2 \u00d7 2 GB) or 8 GB (2 \u00d7 4 GB)</span>\n|colspan=2| 4&nbsp;GB (2 \u00d7 2&nbsp;GB)<br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional 8 GB (2 \u00d7 4 GB)</span>\n|colspan=3| 4&nbsp;GB (2 \u00d7 2&nbsp;GB)<br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional 8 GB (2 \u00d7 4 GB) or 16 GB (2 \u00d7 8 GB)''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/mac-mini/features.html |title=Mac mini 2012 features |quote=Mac mini comes with 4GB of fast 1600MHz DDR3 memory. And thanks to a removable bottom panel, it's easy to add more |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130104110527/http://www.apple.com/mac-mini/features.html |archivedate=January 4, 2013 }}</ref></span>\n|colspan=1| 4&nbsp;GB soldered on board<ref name=\"cant upgrade memory\">{{cite web | url = http://www.macrumors.com/2014/10/17/mac-mini-soldered-ram/ | title = New 2014 Mac mini Has Soldered RAM, Not User Replaceable | url-status = live | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141020033023/http://www.macrumors.com/2014/10/17/mac-mini-soldered-ram/ | archivedate = October 20, 2014 | df = mdy-all }}</ref><br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional 8 GB or 16 GB available at time of purchase only''</span>\n|colspan=2| 8&nbsp;GB soldered on board<ref name=\"cant upgrade memory\" /><br /><span style=\"color:#969696\">''Optional 16 GB available at time of purchase only''</span>\n|-\n|colspan=2|1066&nbsp;MHz [[DDR3 SDRAM]]\n|colspan=3|1333&nbsp;MHz [[DDR3 SDRAM]]\n|colspan=6|1600&nbsp;MHz DDR3 SDRAM<ref name=\"memory_upgrades\">{{cite web|url=https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT205041|title=Mac mini: How to remove or install memory|website=apple.com|accessdate=November 3, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116055020/https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT205041|archive